cs.LG, cs.CR, cs.CY, cs.AI, cs.SI

This paper discusses the use of algorithms in decision making, specifically in the context of pretrial release decisions. It also focuses on the issue of algorithmic fairness and proposes a constrained optimization approach to address racial disparities. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), as the paper discusses the potential biases and risks associated with algorithmic decision making. The paper also touches upon topics related to cybernetics (cs.CY), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and social and information networks (cs.SI), which are also possible categories.
